    <!-- Quantification Playbook -->
    <section id="quantification" class="py-12 md:py-16 bg-warm">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
        <p class="text-secondary text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-2">Before You Start</p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl text-primary mb-3">How to Turn Fuzzy Achievements Into Hard Numbers</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed mb-8">Most people undersell their impact because they think they need exact data. You don't. You need defensible estimates. Here are six frameworks to quantify work that feels hard to measure.</p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <!-- Framework 1 -->
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-primary/[0.06] p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-secondary/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-secondary" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/></svg>
              </div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary text-sm">Time Saved = Money Saved</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="text-text-muted text-xs leading-relaxed mb-2">If you saved your CEO 5 hours a week, and they earn $500K, that's $120K/year in recovered executive time. The formula:</p>
            <div class="bg-cream rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-xs font-mono text-primary">(hours saved/week) x 52 x (exec annual comp / 2,080) = annual value</div>
          </div>

          <!-- Framework 2 -->
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-primary/[0.06] p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-secondary/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-secondary" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z"/></svg>
              </div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary text-sm">Error Prevention = Risk Avoided</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="text-text-muted text-xs leading-relaxed mb-2">Processing $10M/month at 99% vs. 95% accuracy? That's $4.8M in prevented errors per year. Even small accuracy gains are massive at volume.</p>
            <div class="bg-cream rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-xs font-mono text-primary">(volume) x (old error rate - new error rate) x (avg transaction) = risk avoided</div>
          </div>

          <!-- Framework 3 -->
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-primary/[0.06] p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-secondary/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-secondary" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z"/></svg>
              </div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary text-sm">Stakeholder Scale = Complexity Managed</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="text-text-muted text-xs leading-relaxed mb-2">200+ stakeholders across 7 markets isn't just a number. It's thousands of touchpoints per year. Each one is a potential miscommunication you prevented.</p>
            <div class="bg-cream rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-xs font-mono text-primary">(stakeholders) x (touchpoints/month) x 12 x (minutes each) / 60 = hours managed/year</div>
          </div>

          <!-- Framework 4 -->
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-primary/[0.06] p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-secondary/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-secondary" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7h8m0 0v8m0-8l-8 8-4-4-6 6"/></svg>
              </div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary text-sm">Process Efficiency = Compounding Gains</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="text-text-muted text-xs leading-relaxed mb-2">A process that saves 30 minutes per use, used by 10 people, 4 times a month? That's 240 hours saved per year. And it keeps working after you leave.</p>
            <div class="bg-cream rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-xs font-mono text-primary">(time saved per use) x (users) x (frequency/month) x 12 = annual hours saved</div>
          </div>

          <!-- Framework 5 -->
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-primary/[0.06] p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-secondary/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-secondary" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M18.364 5.636l-3.536 3.536m0 5.656l3.536 3.536M9.172 9.172L5.636 5.636m3.536 9.192l-3.536 3.536M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/></svg>
              </div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary text-sm">Faster Ramp-Up = Faster Revenue</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="text-text-muted text-xs leading-relaxed mb-2">Every month a new hire is "ramping up" is a month at reduced productivity. Cut ramp from 4 months to 3 months for a $90K hire? That's $7,500 in recovered productivity.</p>
            <div class="bg-cream rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-xs font-mono text-primary">(months saved) x (salary / 12) x (productivity gap %, usually 50%) = value per hire</div>
          </div>

          <!-- Framework 6 -->
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-primary/[0.06] p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-secondary/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-secondary" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 21V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v16m14 0h2m-2 0h-5m-9 0H3m2 0h5M9 7h1m-1 4h1m4-4h1m-1 4h1m-5 10v-5a1 1 0 011-1h2a1 1 0 011 1v5m-4 0h4"/></svg>
              </div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary text-sm">Budget Optimization = Direct Savings</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="text-text-muted text-xs leading-relaxed mb-2">This one is straightforward. If you managed a $200K event budget and cut costs by 15%, that's $30K saved. The key is knowing the total budget, not just the percentage.</p>
            <div class="bg-cream rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-xs font-mono text-primary">(budget) x (% reduction) = direct savings</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-primary/[0.06] p-5 mt-6">
          <p class="text-primary text-sm font-medium mb-2">The rule of thumb for everything below</p>
          <p class="text-text-muted text-xs leading-relaxed">If you don't know the exact number, estimate conservatively and say "at least" or "approximately." A conservative estimate is always more credible than a round number or a guess. "Saved approximately $45K in executive time" beats "saved time" every single time.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

